We=E2=80=99re used to immigration. We believe in immigration. You can=E2=80=
=99t walk down the street anywhere and not run into people who look differe=
nt than you, maybe have a slight accent or come from a different place. The=
y can=E2=80=99t do immigration in Japan. And guess what=E2=80=99s happening=
? Birth rates are falling in all these wealthy countries. You need immigrat=
ion to do well, and we should take advantage of our big advantage in the wo=
rld.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Yet Donald Trump is doing exactly the opposite. It will hurt our economy an=
d it is hurting people across the country. Let=E2=80=99s throw the violent =
criminals who are undocumented out. Let=E2=80=99s keep the people who are l=
aw-abiding and working and paying taxes.

Breaking the Cycle
------------------

Part of your brand is talking about kitchen table issues, wages, helping wo=
rking
families=E2=80=94topics that are pretty much Democratic dogma. But again, R=
epublicans won on the economy last year. And now that he=E2=80=99s back in =
the White House, Trump swallows every news cycle with culture-war topics an=
d attacks and jokes and endless outrage bait. How in the world can Democrat=
s offer a contrast message against Trump on middle-class issues in this att=
ention economy?=C2=A0

=C2=A0

How about simple,
clear answers? We want to raise wages for middle-class, working-class Ameri=
cans. That=E2=80=99s a very simple message. We want to lower costs. They wa=
nt to lower taxes for the wealthiest Americans. Their actions prove that th=
ey don=E2=80=99t want to lower costs. Have you seen anything about lowering=
 costs in these first few days, with hundreds of memos and executive orders=
? Nothing. Right? It=E2=80=99s all the culture wars they=E2=80=99re attacki=
ng on. Give me a break. D.E.I. is the cause of an aviation collision? This =
is a
distraction. That=E2=80=99s what they=E2=80=99re all about.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Let=E2=80=99s raise the minimum wage. That=E2=80=99s a simple message. Let=
=E2=80=99s make sure people get healthcare. Everybody deserves healthcare. =
We should win on that issue. We should win on wages. Look, you don=E2=80=99=
t have to talk about everything that they=E2=80=99re doing. But you do have=
 to talk about basic rights, civil rights, and you have to talk about how t=
o make people=E2=80=99s lives
easier at the kitchen table. Make it easier for them to pay their bills, pu=
t their kids through college, and save for retirement. I think those are si=
mple things. You can pick a few of those if you think that=E2=80=99s too ma=
ny topics, but that=E2=80=99s what we should be talking about. That=E2=80=
=99s what I=E2=80=99ve been executing on. Literally. I mean, we eliminated =
the grocery tax in our state. That=E2=80=99s simple. How about that as a wa=
y to lower people=E2=80=99s costs when they go to the grocery store? You ha=
ven=E2=80=99t heard any of that
from Donald Trump.

=C2=A0

Glenn Youngkin, a Republican governor in my home state, Virginia, did that =
too. Okay, last question before you go. Chicago sports hot seat. Is Caleb W=
illiams a bust?

=C2=A0

All right. I=E2=80=99m not going into that. Great to talk to you. Bye.

