ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;"><strong><em>Peter Hamby</em></strong><strong>: For the first few weeks =
of Trump=E2=80=99s
presidency, a lot of prominent Democrats have seemed to be lying low. Maybe=
 they=E2=80=99re cowed, or timid, or maybe they=E2=80=99re just unsure how =
to shadowbox an incoming president who won an unambiguous victory. But afte=
r Trump=E2=80=99s executive order freezing federal spending, you came out s=
winging pretty hard. And you=E2=80=99ve ramped that up even more since Trum=
p tied the plane crash over Reagan National to D.E.I. What=E2=80=99s motiva=
ting you here?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0<=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>J.B. Pritzker</em>: These p=
eople have no idea what average working Americans are going through. They=
=E2=80=99re sitting in some room with the culture warriors coming up with l=
ines that they can throw out there that might incite people, but they have =
no idea. I mean, people really are suffering. They need higher wages, they =
need lower costs. These are things [Republicans] articulated during the cam=
paign better than Democrats did. And now here we are, nearly two
weeks into the Trump administration, and they=E2=80=99ve thrown everything =
out there to cause a lot of chaos, but nothing that actually benefits worki=
ng people. They started with having the wealthiest people in America sittin=
g in the front row as he=E2=80=99s taking the oath of office. And I think t=
hat tells you everything you need to know.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-b=
ottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Remember: He=
 hired a bunch of these Project 2025 types, who actually worked for
Heritage Foundation. They don=E2=80=99t know how to run the government. The=
y have ideas that they <em>think</em> will work. They have radical right-wi=
ng, crazy thoughts about how they should remake America. The reality is tha=
t those things=E2=80=94some of =E2=80=99em are unconstitutional, many are i=
llegal=E2=80=94but they don=E2=80=99t actually know how to effectuate thing=
s that help people. In the meantime, underlying a lot of it is the taking a=
way of people=E2=80=99s civil rights, and that=E2=80=99s dangerous.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:
0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Give me a =
specific example of how they=E2=80=99re taking away civil rights.</strong><=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">Well, how about the fight to protect people=E2=80=99s i=
ndividual rights, whether you=E2=80=99re LGBTQ or you=E2=80=99re Black or y=
ou=E2=80=99re Latino? I mean, birthright citizenship=E2=80=94how about that=
 for an example? It=E2=80=99s a basic civil right, a constitutional right, =
and we know his order is
unconstitutional. By the way, what Republicans say about it is, <em>Well ye=
ah, we know it=E2=80=99s unconstitutional, but it=E2=80=99s the right idea.=
 </em>Wait a minute!</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>With Democrats, it feels l=
ike there is a leadership vacuum that needs to be filled. You were one of t=
he few Dem governors to come out and condemn the January 6th pardons and cl=
emencies, pretty loudly. But otherwise, it feels like Democrats are
being very cautious right now, and there=E2=80=99s room for someone out the=
re to fill the leadership vacuum.=C2=A0</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;ma=
rgin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Let me=
 begin by saying I was governor in the last two years of the last Trump adm=
inistration, so I have lived through how to protect our state in the contex=
t of a president who wants to take people=E2=80=99s freedoms away and doesn=
=E2=80=99t give a damn about average everyday working Americans. And of
course, at the beginning of Covid, we literally had to protect people=E2=80=
=99s lives from what they were doing in Washington. So I bring that to the =
fight.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I don=E2=80=99t know why anybody doesn=E2=
=80=99t understand that, in his first administration, Trump came in with al=
l of his crazy ideas, but tried to hire people to run the government who we=
re sort of in the Republican Party and had some experience running things. =
This
time, everybody knew if he won, he was going to put in only the most loyal =
people, the biggest MAGA advocates, and they=E2=80=99re going to be in char=
ge of everything. And guess what=E2=80=99s happening? Project 2025, which h=
e said he disavowed, that=E2=80=99s exactly the playbook they=E2=80=99re fo=
llowing. It is going to be an onslaught against the things that we hold mos=
t dear. Fighting for working-class Americans and the most vulnerable. Did y=
ou not know that he was coming after Medicaid? Of course he was!=C2=A0</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">So=
 look, I really believe that Americans are being lied to. They were lied to=
 during his campaign about what he was all about here. Does corporate Ameri=
ca need a tax cut from 24 percent to 15 percent? Doesn=E2=80=99t a working =
family need the tax cut? And all the things that he wants to cut=E2=80=94Me=
dicaid, Meals on Wheels, programs that support police=E2=80=94all those thi=
ngs he wants to cut, why is he doing it? Because he wants to give a massive=
 tax
cut to <strong>Elon Musk</strong> and the wealthiest Americans.</p></div>
